        <!-- English Policy -->
        <div id="policy-en" class="policy">
            <p><strong>DrunkWalking</strong> respects your privacy. This policy explains how we handle your information.</p>
            
            <div class="highlight">
                <p><strong>TL;DR: We don't collect any personal data. Everything stays on your device.</strong></p>
            </div>

            <h2>1. Information Collection</h2>
            <p>We <strong>do not collect any personal information</strong>. No sign-up, no login, no servers — all data stays locally on your iPhone.</p>

            <h2>2. Sensor Data</h2>
            <p>This app uses gyroscope and accelerometer to detect spins, steps, and walking deviation — all to create the "drunk simulation" experience. Sensor data is:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Read in real-time only while you use the app</li>
                <li>Processed and immediately discarded</li>
                <li>Never recorded, stored, or saved</li>
                <li>Never leaves your device</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>3. Local Storage</h2>
            <p>Player names and game scores you enter are stored locally on your device (using Apple's CoreData). This data:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Is only used to display scoreboards and history</li>
                <li>Is never accessed by us or any third party</li>
                <li>Can be deleted anytime by tapping "Clear Tonight" on the Scoreboard screen</li>
                <li>Will be completely removed if you uninstall the app</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>4. Third-Party Services</h2>
            <p>We <strong>do not use</strong> any third-party analytics, advertising SDKs, crash reporters, or data collection services. The app works completely offline and requires no internet permission.</p>

            <h2>5. Data Sharing</h2>
            <p>We <strong>do not</strong> share, sell, rent, or trade any of your information — simply because we don't collect any.</p>

            <h2>6. Children's Privacy</h2>
            <p>We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. Since we collect nothing at all, there's no risk of children's data being collected. If you're a parent with concerns, contact us at the email below.</p>

            <h2>7. Changes to This Policy</h2>
            <p>We may update this privacy policy occasionally. Any changes will be reflected by updating the "Last Updated" date at the top. We encourage you to review this page periodically.</p>

            <h2>8. Contact Us</h2>
            <p>If you have any questions about this privacy policy, please reach out:</p>
            <p>📧 <a href="mailto:a1012927404@gmail.com">a1012927404@gmail.com</a></p>

            <hr>

            <p style="font-size: 15px; color: #6b6b70;">This policy is effective as of March 15, 2024.</p>
